description:
Check out the launch trailer for Sins of a Solar Empire 2, a galactic sci-fi real-time 4X strategy game developed by Ironclad Games Corporation and Stardock Entertainment. Players will explore, expand, exploit, and exterminate those worthy through the might of a military force. Engage in activities such as diplomacy, trade, culture, influence, and more to expand influence and power. Sins of a Solar Empire 2 is available now for PC (Steam).

description:
Take a look at the release date trailer for Age of Empires Mobile, an immersive mobile medieval war strategy game developed by Xbox Game Studios and TiMi Studios. Players will build their empire in a lively, realistic medieval world featuring stunning civilizations, imperial cities, and historical figures. Encounter realistic and interactive terrain and weather and manage multiple troops with real-time micro-control. Age of Empires Mobile is launching on October 17 for iOS and Android.

title: Age of Empires Mobile - Official Release Date Announcement Trailer

description:
Goodrich is a comedy-drama distributed by Ketchup Entertainment.

Andy Goodrich’s life is upended when his wife and mother of their nine-year-old twins enters a 90-day rehab program, leaving him on his own with their young kids. Thrust into the world of modern parenthood, Goodrich leans on his daughter from his first marriage, Grace (Mila Kunis), as he ultimately evolves into the father Grace never had.

Goodrich stars Michael Keaton, Mila Kunis, Carmen Ejogo, Michael Urie, Kevin Pollak, Viven Lyra Blair, Nico Haraga, Danny Deferrari with Lauren Benanti and Andie MacDowell. The film is written and directed by Hallie Meyers-Shyer alongside being produced by Daniela Taplin Lundberg, Kevin Mann, and Dave Caplan. Goodrich is executively produced by Michael Keaton, Amy Pascal, and Mila Kunis.

Goodrich is in theaters on October 18.

#Goodrich #MichaelKeaton #MilaKunis
title: Goodrich - Official Trailer (2024) Michael Keaton, Mila Kunis

description:
Take a look at the Mai Xiaowen Operator reveal trailer for Delta Force: Hawk Ops, an upcoming free-to-play action first-person shooter developed by Timi Studio. Mai Xiaowen, callsign Hackclaw, is a Recon Operator skilled with electronics with her Signal Decoder and Flash Drone to locate and flush out the enemy. Mai Xiaowen is available now as part of the ongoing PC Alpha Test with the game launching soon for PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, iOS, Android, and PC.

description:
Watch the Lance weapon overview guide for Monster Hunter Wilds, the latest installment in the third-person action co-op hunting game franchise developed by Capcom. Players will be able to use the Lance, a weapon with a top-in-class defense that has the ability to execute a variety of guard-related moves and counters. With Focus Mode, go on the offensive and charge forward by exploiting the monster's weak points. Monster Hunter Wilds is launching in 2025 for PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, and PC (Steam).

description:
Hold your pulse rifle and motion tracker ready, because Alien: Romulus is now in theaters. The newest entry in the long-running sci-fi horror franchise comes from director Fede Álvarez, best known for 2013’s Evil Dead remake and the original horror film Don’t Breathe. The acclaimed director takes the Alien series back to its roots by calling back to the 1979 original with another nail-biting, blood-soaked, haunted house in space. However, the new movie also left us with some serious questions, which we’ll try our best to answer here.

Whether you’re a Weyland-Yutani veteran or if this is your first time in zero gravity, we have the Alien questions (and answers?) you’ve been waiting for. Here are the topics we delve into in this video, but beware of spoilers from this point on!

Again, spoilers follow...

You're still here? OK, here come the Alien: Romulus spoilers...

-What Happened to the Xenomorph From Alien 1979?

-Why Do the Alien Movie Heroes Have a Spaceship if They’re Not Allow
title: Alien: Romulus - The 10 Biggest Burning Questions
